vania</a> • <a href="/Rhode_Island" title="Rhode Island">Rhode Island</a> • <a href="/South_Carolina" title="South Carolina">South Carolina</a> • <a href="/South_Dakota" title="South Dakota">South Dakota</a> • <a href="/Tennessee" title="Tennessee">Tennessee</a> • <a href="/Texas" title="Texas">Texas</a> • <a href="/Utah" title="Utah">Utah</a> • <a href="/Vermont" title="Vermont">Vermont</a> • <a href="/Virginia" title="Virginia">Virginia</a> • <a href="/Washington" title="Washington">Washington</a> • <a href="/West_Virginia" title="West Virginia">West Virginia</a> • <a href="/Wisconsin" title="Wisconsin">Wisconsin</a> • <a href="/Wyoming" title="Wyoming">Wyoming</a></center>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>A <b>U.S. state</b> is any one of the 50 sub-national entities of the United States. 
</p><p>Additionally, there are five <a href="/U.S._Territories" title="U.S. Territories">U.S. territories</a>—American Samoa, Guam, the Northern Mariana Islands, Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands—and Washington, D.C.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
